   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('Customer_Satisfaction.csv')\n",
    "# Define age brackets\n",
    "bins = [18, 30, 45, 60, df['Age'].max()]\n",
    "labels = ['18-30', '31-45', '46-60', '61+']\n",
    "df['AgeBracket'] = pd.cut(df['Age'], bins=bins, labels=labels, right=True, include_lowest=True)\n",
    "# Count travellers in each bracket\n",
    "age_bracket_counts = df['AgeBracket'].value_counts().sort_index()\n",
    "print(\"Travellers in each age bracket:\")\n",
    "print(age_bracket_counts)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('Customer_Satisfaction.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check any null values in 'Travel Class' or 'Seat Comfort' columns\n",
    "null_value_cnt = df[['Travel Class', 'Seat Comfort']].isnull().sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check value counts for 'Travel Class' and fill missing values with mode if any\n",
    "if (null_value_cnt['Travel Class'] > 0):\n",
    "    df['Travel Class'].fillna(df['Travel Class'].mode()[0], inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check value counts for 'Seat Comfort' and fill missing values with mean if any\n",
    "if (null_value_cnt['Seat Comfort'] > 0):\n",
    "    df['Seat Comfort'].fillna(df['Seat Comfort'].mean(), inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check average rating for seat comfort across different travel classes\n",
    "avg_seat_comfort = df.groupby('Travel Class')['Seat Comfort'].mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Average rating for seat comfort across different travel classes:\")\n",
    "print(round(avg_seat_comfort,2))"
   ]

   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('Customer_Satisfaction.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check any null values in 'Travel Class' or 'Food' columns\n",
    "null_value_cnt = df[['Travel Class', 'Food']].isnull().sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "# # Check value counts for 'Travel Class' and fill missing values with mode if any\n",
    "if (null_value_cnt['Travel Class'] > 0):\n",
    "    df['Travel Class'].fillna(df['Travel Class'].mode()[0], inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# # Check value counts for 'Food' and fill missing values with mean if any\n",
    "if (null_value_cnt['Food'] > 0):\n",
    "    df['Food'].fillna(df['Food'].mean(), inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Rating for food across Business and Economy classes\n",
    "food_rating = df[df['Travel Class'].isin(['Business', 'Economy'])].groupby('Travel Class')['Food'].mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Average rating for food across Business and Economy classes:\")\n",
    "print(round(food_rating,2))"
   ]
  },
